#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/introduction.rst:4
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "简介"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/introduction.rst:6
msgid ""
"An Armature in Blender can be thought of as similar to the armature of a real "
"skeleton, and just like a real skeleton an Armature can consist of many bones. "
"These bones can be moved around and anything that they are attached to or "
"associated with will move and deform in a similar way."
msgstr ""
"Blender 中的骨架类似于真实的骨架，就如一个真实的骨架那样，骨架是由许多骨骼组成。"
"这些骨骼可以四处移动，并且它们附着的或相关联的任何东西都将以类似的方式移动和变"
"形。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/introduction.rst:11
msgid ""
"An \"armature\" is a type of object used for :doc:`rigging </rigging/index>`. A "
"rig is the controls and strings that move a marionette (puppet). Armature object "
"borrows many ideas from real life skeletons."
msgstr ""
"\"骨架(armature)\"是用于 :doc:`绑定 </rigging/index>` 的物体类型。绑定是木偶（傀"
"儡）的控制器和牵线。骨架物体借鉴了真实骨架的许多特点。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/introduction.rst:17
msgid "Your first armature"
msgstr "Your first armature 你的第一个骨架"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/introduction.rst:19
msgid ""
"In order to see what we are talking about, let us try to add the default "
"armature in Blender."
msgstr "为了看看我们在谈论什么，让我们尝试在Blender中添加默认的骨架。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/introduction.rst:21
msgid ""
"(Note that armature editing details are explained in the :doc:`armatures editing "
"section </rigging/armatures/bones/editing/index>`)."
msgstr ""
"(需要注意的是骨架的编辑细节说明在  :doc:`armatures editing section </rigging/"
"armatures/bones/editing/index>` 骨架的编辑章节部分）。"

